Jeanette Chabalala, News24FILE: (RescueTech, Supplied to News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; Three women have been rescued by community members after they fell down a cliff in Camperdown near Injabulo clinic in KwaZulu-Natal, paramedics said on Sunday.The incident happened on Sunday afternoon at about 14:40, said emergency services spokesperson Robert Mackenzie.&nbsp;Members of the community used ladders and ropes to free the women. They initiated the rescue after hearing the women calling from down the cliff, he said. &nbsp;When KZN emergency services arrived, the women were already rescued from the cliff. One woman had sustained serious injuries and two of them had minor injuries. The women were transported to hospital for further medical attention. &nbsp;3 woman have been rescued by community members, using ladders&amp; ropes, after they fell down a cliff in Camperdown, earlier this afternoon.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.